The paper discusses a logical approach to explain issues concerning control codes that are independent of the details of the behaviours that are controlled. This suggests a focus on the abstract and theoretical aspects of programming, which is likely to fall under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine structures, which could also place it under Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Software Engineering (cs.SE). The example given about the production of a new compiler from an existing one suggests a focus on Architecture (cs.AR) or Systems and Control (cs.SY).
